7 Major Traditional Weaving Techniques in India 1. Banarasi Weaving (Uttar Pradesh) One of the most famous weaving traditions, Banarasi silk is known for its gold and silver brocade (zari), intricate patterns, and Mughal-inspired motifs. 2. Kanjeevaram Weaving (Tamil Nadu) Woven from pure mulberry silk, Kanjeevaram sarees are renowned for their durability, bold colors, and temple border designs.¤